that worked for people.

00:45:39.540 --> 00:45:41.690
Whether it was ignoring
those distractions,

00:45:41.690 --> 00:45:45.712
or making a note of
them, and what works.

00:45:45.712 --> 00:45:46.670
SHARON SALZBERG: Great.

00:45:46.670 --> 00:45:52.344
So what tends to work is
ritualizing kinds of pauses.

00:45:52.344 --> 00:45:54.010
You know, they don't--
well, two things.

00:45:54.010 --> 00:45:57.850
One is uni-tasking every now and
then, instead of multitasking.

00:45:57.850 --> 00:46:00.260
And the other is
ritualizing certain pauses.

00:46:00.260 --> 00:46:05.580
They don't have to be--
neither has to be very lengthy.

00:46:05.580 --> 00:46:09.480
But, we need them to
punctuate our day.

00:46:09.480 --> 00:46:12.890
So that they're repeated.

00:46:12.890 --> 00:46:17.380
And in terms of
pauses, for example

00:46:17.380 --> 00:46:21.000
a very classic example
would be don't pick up

00:46:21.000 --> 00:46:22.840
the phone on the first ring.

00:46:22.840 --> 00:46:24.920
Let it ring three
times, and breath.

00:46:24.920 --> 00:46:26.130
And then you pick it up.

00:46:26.130 --> 00:46:29.100
It's almost unbearable
to think about.

00:46:29.100 --> 00:46:35.930
But if you actually do it,
it's like-- in those moments,

00:46:35.930 --> 00:46:37.840
we can return to ourselves.

00:46:37.840 --> 00:46:41.190
Because usually what
happens, as you are implying,

00:46:41.190 --> 00:46:44.010
is that we get caught in
this kind of crazy momentum.

00:46:44.010 --> 00:46:47.204
And we're taken so far away
from ourselves that we're just--

00:46:47.204 --> 00:46:48.870
and we're getting
increasingly agitated,

00:46:48.870 --> 00:46:51.210
and then it's harder
to return because we

00:46:51.210 --> 00:46:54.030
know it's going to feel
comfortable when we come back.

00:46:54.030 --> 00:46:57.140
But if we just kind of
regularly come back.

00:46:57.140 --> 00:46:58.510
We come back to the moment.

00:46:58.510 --> 00:46:59.770
We come back to ourselves.

00:46:59.770 --> 00:47:01.810
We can utilize something
like the breath, which

00:47:01.810 --> 00:47:04.000
is with us-- I was
going to say always,

00:47:04.000 --> 00:47:09.546
except I learned in doing
an interview for this book,

00:47:09.546 --> 00:47:13.730
the journalist told me there
was such a thing as email apnea.

00:47:13.730 --> 00:47:15.690
Which I hadn't known before.

00:47:15.690 --> 00:47:18.460
That people tend to stop
breathing, actually,

00:47:18.460 --> 00:47:19.085
checking email.

00:47:22.140 --> 00:47:27.410
Which is also interesting,
and kind of dreadful.

00:47:27.410 --> 00:47:30.370
But, since we're breathing
most of the time,

00:47:30.370 --> 00:47:33.780
and we could be breathing
more if we're mindful,

00:47:33.780 --> 00:47:36.310
it's a great vehicle
for just coming back.

00:47:36.310 --> 00:47:39.920
And once we come back to the
moment, and to ourselves,

00:47:39.920 --> 00:47:42.507
we're also coming back to
our sense of priorities,

00:47:42.507 --> 00:47:43.340
our sense of values.

00:47:43.340 --> 00:47:46.472
They're just apparent to
us, whereas they're not

00:47:46.472 --> 00:47:48.430
when we're just kind of
caught in the momentum.

00:47:48.430 --> 00:47:50.740
And then uni-tasking.

00:47:50.740 --> 00:47:53.460
I'm sure you know studies
show that multitasking isn't

00:47:53.460 --> 00:47:55.300
as great as what
it's made out to be,

00:47:55.300 --> 00:47:57.470
in that we're actually
not more effective,

00:47:57.470 --> 00:47:59.720
we're not more efficient,
we're not getting more done.

00:47:59.720 --> 00:48:02.610
So even though we've got
this huge amount to do,

00:48:02.610 --> 00:48:05.290
and it seems like it will
get done the best if we do it

00:48:05.290 --> 00:48:08.880
all at once, it's not going
to happen in a good way.

00:48:08.880 --> 00:48:11.680
And so, here too,
it's like a question

00:48:11.680 --> 00:48:13.370
of ritualizing or committing.

00:48:13.370 --> 00:48:17.320
Like three times a day, if
I'm drinking a cup of tea,

00:48:17.320 --> 00:48:20.690
or drinking a cup of coffee,
I'm going to just do that.

00:48:20.690 --> 00:48:22.740
I'm not going to do
that, and check my email,

00:48:22.740 --> 00:48:27.040
and have a phone conversation,
and watch the news on TV.

00:48:27.040 --> 00:48:30.910
And if we if we can get into
that habit of just bringing

00:48:30.910 --> 00:48:34.030
mindfulness in these short
momen-- one of my teachers

00:48:34.030 --> 00:48:37.400
said short moments
many times-- then it

00:48:37.400 --> 00:48:39.184
will make a very big difference.

